    "reasoning": "1. **State Identification**: The Lemming can be in several logical states: Walking Left, Walking Right, Falling (while remembering direction), Digging (while remembering direction), and Splattered. \n2. **Refined States**: \n   - `WALK_LEFT`: Walking left on ground.\n   - `WALK_RIGHT`: Walking right on ground.\n   - `FALL_LEFT`: Falling, was walking left.\n   - `FALL_RIGHT`: Falling, was walking right.\n   - `DIG_LEFT`: Digging, was walking left.\n   - `DIG_RIGHT`: Digging, was walking right.\n   - `SPLAT`: Permanent terminal state.\n3. **Transition Logic**:\n   - From `WALK_LEFT`: \n     - If `ground == 0`: transition to `FALL_LEFT` (start fall counter).\n     - Else if `dig == 1`: transition to `DIG_LEFT`.\n     - Else if `bump_right == 1`: transition to `WALK_RIGHT`.\n     - Else if `bump_left == 1`: stay `WALK_LEFT` (bumped on the same side).\n     - Special case: `bump_left && bump_right` switches direction (to `WALK_RIGHT`).\n   - From `FALL_...`: \n     - Increment fall counter.\n     - If `ground == 1`: \n       - If `counter > 20`: transition to `SPLAT`.\n       - Else: transition back to `WALK_...` (direction preserved).\n   - From `DIG_...`: \n     - If `ground == 0`: transition to `FALL_...` (direction preserved).\n   - From `SPLAT`: stay `SPLAT`.\n4. **Fall Counter**: Needs to track cycles spent falling. A counter is needed for the `FALL` states. The specification says 'if a Lemming falls for more than 20 clock cycles then hits the ground'. This means if the time between `ground=0` and `ground=1` is > 20, it splats. \n5. **Precedence**: The spec states: 'fall has higher precedence than dig, which has higher precedence than switching directions.' This is handled by the order of `if-else` in the combinational logic.\n6. **Implementation Details**: Use an asynchronous reset for `areset`. Use a counter for falling duration. All outputs are Moore outputs (based on current state).",
    "module": "module TopModule(\n    input  logic clk,\n    input  logic areset,\n    input  logic bump_left,\n    input  logic bump_right,\n    input  logic ground,\n    input  logic dig,\n    output logic walk_left,\n    output logic walk_right,\n    output logic aaah,\n    output logic digging\n);\n\n    // State definitions\n    localparam WALK_LEFT  = 3'd0;\n    localparam WALK_RIGHT = 3'd1;\n    localparam FALL_LEFT  = 3'd2;\n    localparam FALL_RIGHT = 3'd3;\n    localparam DIG_LEFT   = 3'd4;\n    localparam DIG_RIGHT  = 3'd5;\n    localparam SPLAT      = 3'd6;\n\n    logic [2:0] state;\n    logic [7:0] fall_counter; // Sufficient to count > 20\n\n    // Sequential logic\n    always @(posedge clk or posedge areset) begin\n        if (areset) begin\n            state <= WALK_LEFT;\n            fall_counter <= 8'd0;\n        end else begin\n            case (state)\n                WALK_LEFT:\n                    if (!ground) begin\n                        state <= FALL_LEFT;\n                        fall_counter <= 8'd0;\n                    end else if (dig) begin\n                        state <= DIG_LEFT;\n                    end else if (bump_right || (bump_left && bump_right)) begin\n                        state <= WALK_RIGHT;\n                    end\n\n                WALK_RIGHT:\n                    if (!ground) begin\n                        state <= FALL_RIGHT;\n                        fall_counter <= 8'd0;\n                    end else if (dig) begin\n                        state <= DIG_RIGHT;\n                    end else if (bump_left || (bump_left && bump_right)) begin\n                        state <= WALK_LEFT;\n                    end\n\n                FALL_LEFT:\n                    if (ground) begin\n                        if (fall_counter > 8'd20) begin\n                            state <= SPLAT;\n                        end else begin\n                            state <= WALK_LEFT;\n                        end\n                    end else begin\n                        fall_counter <= fall_counter + 8'd1;\n                    end\n\n                FALL_RIGHT:\n                    if (ground) begin\n                        if (fall_counter > 8'd20) begin\n                            state <= SPLAT;\n                        end else begin\n                            state <= WALK_RIGHT;\n                        end\n                    end else begin\n                        fall_counter <= fall_counter + 8'd1;\n                    end\n\n                DIG_LEFT:\n                    if (!ground) begin\n                        state <= FALL_LEFT;\n                        fall_counter <= 8'd0;\n                    end\n\n                DIG_RIGHT:\n                    if (!ground) begin\n                        state <= FALL_RIGHT;\n                        fall_counter <= 8'd0;\n                    end\n\n                SPLAT:\n                    state <= SPLAT;\n\n                default:\n                    state <= WALK_LEFT;\n            endcase\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Moore Output Logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        walk_left = 1'b0;\n        walk_right = 1'b0;\n        aaah = 1'b0;\n        digging = 1'b0;\n\n        case (state) \n            WALK_LEFT:\n                walk_left = 1'b1;\n            WALK_RIGHT:\n                walk_right = 1'b1;\n            FALL_LEFT,\n            FALL_RIGHT:\n                aaah = 1'b1;\n            DIG_LEFT,\n            DIG_RIGHT:\n                digging = 1'b1;\n            SPLAT:\n                begin\n                    walk_left = 1'b0;\n                    walk_right = 1'b0;\n                    aaah = 1'b0;\n                    digging = 1'b0;\n                end\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Special handling for digging output during state transition\n    // The spec says: \"continue digging until it reaches the other side (ground=0)\"\n    // In my state machine, DIG_LEFT/RIGHT handles this. \n    // However, if a Lemming is walking and hits ground=0, it falls. \n    // If it's digging and hits ground=0, it falls. \n    // The 'digging' output should be high during DIG_LEFT/DIG_RIGHT.\n    // Let's refine the Moore logic for DIG state.\n    // In the state machine above, if state is DIG_LEFT, output digging is 1.\n    // If ground becomes 0, state becomes FALL_LEFT in next cycle.\n\nendmodule"
